main event: Two civilian witnesses observed a bright white light coming towards them in Bartlett, New Hampshire on February 26, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared as a round, steady light with a bright white fluorescent appearance, similar to a dark center area surrounded by a halo.
The object was observed for approximately 2 miles away.
The disturbed dog was not as large as the moon.
The object appeared to disappear and reappear several times.
The witness described the object as causing static on their car radio at each pass.
sighted object: bright white light, round and steady
